'''Giuliano Simeone Baldini''' (born 18 December 2002) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|Winger]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

==Early life==
Born in [[Rome]] when his father, [[Diego Simeone]], was playing for [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]], Simeone returned to Argentina to live with his mother at the age of four,<ref name=Goal>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/giuliano-simeone-cholo-teenage-son-success-atletico-madrid/z9js5diuim2j12rzwxajj2mnu |title=Giuliano Simeone: Can Cholo's teenage son be a success at Atletico Madrid? |publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=5 October 2021 |accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref> and began his career with [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tycsports.com/river-plate/river-quien-es-giuliano-simeone-el-hijo-que-el-cholo-se-llevo-al-atletico-de-madrid-id402462.html |title=Quién es Giuliano Simeone, el hijo que el Cholo se llevó de River a Atlético de Madrid |trans-title=Who is Giuliano Simeone, the son that ''Cholo'' took from River to Atlético de Madrid |publisher=[[TyC Sports]] |language=es |date=2 January 2022 |accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref> In September 2019, he moved to [[Atlético Madrid]]'s youth categories;<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/en/2019/09/11/soccer/1568196001_199869.html |title=Giuliano Simeone quits River Plate "without permission" to join Atlético de Madrid's youth team |publisher=[[Diario AS]] |date=11 September 2019 |accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref> as he had not signed a professional contract with River, the club was unable to retain him, and the move was later approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name=Marca>{{cite web |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2019/09/12/5d7a6a56268e3e0c238b45db.html |title=FIFA approve Giuliano Simeone's move to Atletico Madrid |publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |date=12 September 2019 |accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref> He then joined the ''Juvenil'' squad.

==Club career==
===Atlético Madrid B===
Simeone made his senior debut with ''Atleti''{{'}}s [[Atlético Madrid B|B-team]] on 17 January 2021, starting and scoring the opener in a 1–1 [[Segunda División B]] away draw against [[UD Poblense]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/futbol/giuliano-simeone-debut-gol-filial-11461189 |title=Giuliano Simeone, debut y gol con el filial del Atlético |trans-title=Giuliano Simeone, debut and goal with Atlético's reserves |publisher=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]] |language=es |date=17 January 2021 |accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref> He scored three further goals in [[2020–21 Segunda División B|the season]], but his team suffered relegation.

After spending the 2021 pre-season with the first team,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/08/09/primera/1628540866_511091.html |title=Giuliano y Javi Serrano sacan con nota la prueba de Simeone |trans-title=Giuliano and Javi Serrano successfully pass through Simeone's trial |publisher=Diario AS |language=es |date=10 August 2021 |accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref> Simeone returned to the B's now in [[Tercera División RFEF]], scoring eight goals in 11 matches between the months of November and December.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/12/26/primera/1640549447_901916.html |title=Giuliano llama a la puerta |trans-title=Giuliano knocks on the door |publisher=Diario AS |language=es |date=26 December 2021 |accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref>

He debuted with the senior [[Atlético Madrid]] side in a 0–0 [[La Liga]] tie with [[Granada CF|Granada]] on 20 April 2022, coming on as a sub in the 91st minute.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.intothecalderon.com/2022/4/20/23034263/giuliano-diego-simeone-atletico-madrid-granada-laliga-debut |title=Giuliano Simeone, Diego's son, makes debut for Atlético Madrid |first=Robbie |last=Dunne |date=20 April 2022 |website=Into the Calderon}}</ref>

===Loans to Real Zaragoza and Alavés===
On 4 July 2022, Simeone was loaned to [[Segunda División]] side [[Real Zaragoza]] for [[2022–23 Segunda División|the season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.realzaragoza.com/noticias/acuerdo-con-el-atl-tico-de-madrid-para-la-cesi-n-de-giuliano-simeone |title=Acuerdo con el Atlético de Madrid para la cesión de Giuliano Simeone |trans-title=Agreement with Atlético de Madrid for the loan of Giuliano Simeone |publisher=Real Zaragoza |language=es |date=4 July 2022 |accessdate=11 July 2022}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal two months later, netting the opener in a 2–1 home loss against [[CD Lugo]].

On 21 July 2023, Simeone renewed his contract with ''Atleti'' until 2028, and moved on loan to [[Deportivo Alavés]] in the top tier, for one year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/acuerdo-con-el-alaves-para-la-cesion-de-giuliano-simeone-quien-renueva-hasta-2028 |title=Acuerdo con el Alavés para la cesión de Giuliano Simeone, quien renueva hasta 2028 |trans-title=Agreement for the loan of Giuliano Simeone, who renews until 2028 |publisher=Atlético Madrid |language=es |date=21 July 2023 |accessdate=21 July 2023}}</ref> On 6 August, during a pre-season [[Exhibition match|friendly]] against [[Burgos CF]], he broke his [[fibula]] and also suffered an [[ankle]] injury after a tackle from [[José Joaquín Matos]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/espana/nota/_/id/12406560/alaves-giuliano-simeone-grave-lesion-amistoso-burgos |title=Se confirmó la grave lesión que sufrió Giuliano Simeone en un amistoso de Alavés |trans-title=The serious injury that Giuliano Simeone suffered in a friendly of Alavés was confirmed |publisher=[[ESPN Deportes]] |language=es |date=7 August 2023 |accessdate=11 August 2023}}</ref>

===Return to Atlético Madrid===
Simeone returned to his parent club, Atlético Madrid, ahead of the 2024–25 season. On 3 November 2024, he scored his first goal for the club in a 2–0 win over [[UD Las Palmas|Las Palmas]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/simeones-son-giuliano-scores-atleticos-2-0-win-over-las-palmas-2024-11-03/ |title=Simeone's son Giuliano scores in Atletico's 2-0 win over Las Palmas |publisher=Reuters |date=3 November 2024}}</ref> On 29 January 2025, he scored his first [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal and provided an assist in a 4–1 away win over [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|RB Salzburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles/salzburg-1-4-atletico-madrid-griezmann-brace-leads-visitors-to-top-eight-finish-2025-01-29 |title=Salzburg 1-4 Atletico Madrid: Griezmann brace leads visitors to top eight finish |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=30 January 2025}}</ref> 

On 15 January 2026, Simeone extended his contract with Atlético Madrid until 30 June 2030.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 January 2026 |title=Giuliano signs contract extension until 2030 |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/giuliano-signs-contract-extension-until-2030 |access-date=16 January 2026 |publisher=[[Atlético Madrid]] |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Simeone competed for [[Argentina at the 2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=SIMEONE Giuliano |url=https://olympics.com/en/paris-2024/athlete/giuliano-simeone_3556435 |work=[[Paris 2024 Olympics]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240730140445/https://olympics.com/en/paris-2024/athlete/giuliano-simeone_3556435 |archive-date=30 July 2024}}</ref>

On 19 November 2024, Simeone debuted for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] against [[Peru national football team|Peru]] in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World cup qualification]].<ref name="eldesmarque">{{Cite web |first=Diego |last=Páez de Roque |title=El idilio de la familia Simeone con la Selección Argentina tras el debut de Giuliano |url=https://www.eldesmarque.com/futbol/internacional/20241120/idilio-simeone-seleccion-argentina-debut-giuliano_300507251.html |website=eldesmarque.com |date=20 November 2024 |access-date=27 March 2025 |language=es}}</ref> In doing so, he became the second son of [[Diego Simeone]] to play for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] after [[Giovanni Simeone]].<ref name="eldesmarque"/> On 25 March 2025, Simeone scored his first goal for Argentina in a 4–1 victory in the same competition against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=La emoción de Giuliano Simeone por su primer gol en la selección Argentina y el festejo con Carolina Baldini |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/deportes/la-emocion-de-giuliano-simeone-por-su-primer-gol-en-la-seleccion-argentina-y-el-festejo-con-carolina-nid26032025/ |newspaper=[[La Nación]] |date=26 March 2025 |access-date=27 March 2025 |language=es}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Simeone is the son of his current manager at Atlético Madrid, [[Diego Simeone]].<ref name=Goal/> His brothers [[Giovanni Simeone|Giovanni]] and [[Gianluca Simeone|Gianluca]] are also footballers.<ref name=Marca/>

